info:
  name: App Basic Tests
  schema: https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json
item:
  - name: Health Check
    request:
      method: GET
      url: '{{baseUrl}}/health'
  - name: Login
    request:
      method: POST
      header:
        - key: Content-Type
          value: application/json
      body:
        mode: raw
        raw: '{ "email": "{{email}}", "password": "{{password}}" }'
      url: '{{baseUrl}}/auth/login'
    event:
      - listen: test
        script:
          exec:
            - let res = pm.response.json();
            - pm.environment.set('token', res.token || res.data?.token);
            - pm.test('Login works', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));
  - name: Profile
    request:
      method: GET
      header:
        - key: Authorization
          value: Bearer {{token}}
      url: '{{baseUrl}}/user/profile'
variable:
  - key: baseUrl
    value: https://api.example.com
  - key: email
    value: test@example.com
  - key: password
    value: Passw0rd!
